The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of thirty-six (36) months.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs of $518.00.  Cash bail to be applied;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) have no contact with William Dorman or his family without the agents approval;
4) provide a DNA sample;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety and no possess or consumption of alcohol or illegal drugs;
8) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
9) AODA assessment and follow through;
10) Complete fifty (50) hours of community service.
The defendant has credit for 2 days if revoked.
The Court denies Atttorney Ditters request for expungement.
$5,000.00 cash bail applied to court costs.  $4,482.00 balance returned to Pazong Yang.
Exhibits 1,2 and 3, photos of defendant.  (in exhibit envelope already in file)
Minutes.
